-- Kenya Power & Lighting Planning Share Split, Rights Offer Before Year End
-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 2010-10-07T04:31:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/kenya-power-lighting-planning-share-split-rights-offer-before-year-end.html
Kenya Power & Lighting Co. Ltd.,
the East African nation’s monopoly power distributor, is
planning a share split under which each share will be divided
into eight before the end of the year.  Directors also approved a rights offer under which holders
will be entitled to purchase 20 new shares for every 51 held,
Managing Director Joseph Njoroge said in a statement published
in the Nairobi-based Daily Nation. In addition, 794.96 million
redeemable non-cumulative shares held by
the Kenyan government will be converted into 76.62 million
oridnary shares, Njoroge said .  “All the above measures are subject to regulatory and
shareholder approvals upon which they are expected to be
implemented before the end of 2010,” he said.  The authorized share capital of Kenya Power Lighting Co.
Ltd. is 18 billion shillings ($223.6 million), out of which 15.9
billion shillings is comprised of non-cumulative preference
shares owned by the government, Njoroge said Nov. 20.  Kenya Power shares closed yesterday at 237 shillings and
have gained 69.3 percent this year. Last month the
companyreported full-year profit climbed 15 percent to 3.72
billion shillings.  To contact the reporter on this story:
